
=Bio=

"Degree in Advertising and Public Relations by the University of Málaga.

Member of the crowdfunding and crowdsourcing open source platform
Goteo.org, where she performs tasks of advice and support for open
crowdfunding campaigns, coordination of matchfunding calls, product
development, training workshops, and representing and promoting the
platform nationally and internationally and now, more and more,
coordinating projects and actions for the internalization of the platform.

Apart from Goteo, she has various experiences in the field of
communication for NGOs and online marketing and has participated in
the development and coordination of projects related to information
technology and digital culture, such as the Traducciones Procomún
project, in the context of the Commons Lab in Medialab-Prado.

She's also quite interested in emerging models and economic
sustainability practices around commons oriented projects, a topic I
began to explore  in January of 2013 through the workstation 'Commons
Economies' in Medialab-Prado, addresing topics like
cryptomoney, cooperativism, collaborative economy, crowdfunding, etc."

